story.title: Out of My League - Episode 1
story.storyDescription: When Auric Alexander—the university tennis star—asks Maria Locanda on a date, she can’t believe her luck. But is it too good to be true?
story.creator: web-uploader
story.prePaywallNotification: Will Maria go on a date with THE Auric Alexander? Keep reading OUT OF MY LEAGUE.
story.postPaywallNotification: OMG! What did Maria see when Auric pulled up for their date? Read episode two of OUT OF MY LEAGUE to find out.

messages.text: Maria Locanda? This is Auric Alexander.
Wait, THE Auric Alexander?
The best tennis player at our school?
The one who’s probably going pro next year?
Why don’t we forget all that stuff about tennis and instead…
Focus on the fact that I sit behind you in our Communications class?
Umm, okay. I didn’t realize you knew my name though.
Of course I do.
I also know that when you’re concentrating, you chew on the end of your pen.
And that your brow crinkles in this really adorable way.
Omg, stop—that’s so embarrassing.
Haha, don’t be embarrassed.
Look, I hope it’s okay I got your number from Stacy.
You know Stacy?
No, but she’s in class with us.
And I guess it wasn’t as hard to go up to her to ask for your number.
It’s just…I always get so nervous when I’m around you.
So I thought it would be easier to text you first.
Wow—this is all so surreal.
But I’m glad you texted me, Auric.
I’m glad too.
Can I take you to dinner sometime?
Sure.
Is tonight too soon?
Actually—no. I’m free.
Good. I’ll pick you up at 7?
Which dorm do you live in?
Winters.
But it’s really far from the Athlete’s dorm
So I can meet you halfway—on the quad.
Don’t be silly. I’ll come to you.
Just to be clear, I want this to be a date.
And that’s why I want to make it special.
Got a dress?
I bet I can scrounge something up 😉
Maria texts her friend Destiny.
OMG, Tini. I need a dress.
Haha, what have you done with my best friend?
She lives in her yoga pants.
I’d get mad at you for saying that if it wasn’t true.
And if I didn’t have a crisis on my hands.
Seriously—I need a dress. STAT.
Yeah, but why?
You’re never going to believe it.
Auric ALEXANDER texted me.
He asked me out to dinner tonight.
THE Auric Alexander?
Yeah. Tini, he’s adorable.
Like, surprisingly shy.
Wait, are you sure you’re talking about Auric Alexander?
The one who’s going pro next year?
The one who looks like Chris Pine?
Yeah…
OMG, I need to cancel.
He’s so out of my league.
I don’t go on dates that require dresses.
I don’t even own a nice dress!
Relax—come over.
You know I have SO many dresses that are about your size.
I’ll lend you one of mine.
Okay, be there in a minute.
Maria races out of her dorm room and down the hall.
She pounds on Destiny’s door, and after Destiny opens it,
Maria tumbles in.
Her voice is squeaky and high, and she can’t stop talking.
I’m totally freaking out.
Wasn’t he dating Kristin Kelly, like, last week?
I don’t look anything like Kristin Kelly.
That girl is so blonde her hair is basically white.
Not to mention, she’s a twig—
And there’s nothing twiggy about this butt.
Haha, well…maybe Auric Alexander wants to tap that.
It’s time for all of us big booty girls to get a chance!
OMG, STOP—I didn’t even think of that.
Do you think Auric is going to expect something?
Especially after this fancy date?
Like…sex?
Don’t be such a loser—he’s a hot athlete.
He’s probably used to girls throwing themselves at him.
Shit! I didn’t even think of that.
I was wrapped up in the fact that I was going on a date with Auric Alexander.
I think I need to cancel.
Maria, you said that already.
Just go, and if you’re getting a weird vibe…
Shut it down and never see him again.
Tini!
Not helping.
Let’s just focus on the dress.
I have a red one that will drive him crazy.
An hour later, Maria is squeezed into a form-fitting dress
That shows off every curve she possesses.
Her hair is swept back in a tight knot,
And her eyes are done up smoky and sultry.
Holy shit.
I don’t even recognize myself.
You look AMAZING.
Girl, I’ve been dying to do your makeup for years.
I’m glad Auric Alexander gave me a chance to finally try.
OMG, he texted six minutes ago!
It says: I’m downstairs. Should I come up?
Shoot, Tini! What do I say?
Just say yes.
Okay—eep! Sent it.
Okay, now GO.
He’s waiting…
Ah, bye! Thank you!
Haha, no problem.
And remember…
You don’t have to do anything you don’t want to do.
But I heard he and Kristin Kelly used to screw on the roof of Klein.
Tini!
Not helping.
Maria’s heart is pounding in her chest
As she takes the elevator down to the lobby.
When the metal doors open, the sight before her
Makes her jaw drop to the floor.
